Now the root cause is much clearer.

The important failure is:

/pkg/bin/appStart.sh: line 454:   144 Terminated $SWM_WD_EXE

This means the watchdog/background process (swmWd.sh or swm.xcg) is getting terminated, and then the main startup script exits, causing the pod restart.

Also this is suspicious:

app coremask is not ready

and later:

EAL: Detected NUMA nodes: 2
EAL: VFIO support initialized

So DPDK initialized partially, but something related to CPU pinning/coremask/watchdog is failing.


---

Most Likely Causes

1. CPU Coremask mismatch (VERY likely)

You requested:

cpu: 26

and app is trying:

taskset 0x20000000000000006

This is a very large CPU mask.

If isolated CPUs / PerformanceProfile do not match expected topology, app exits.


